  "prompt": "How many national parks are in Gujarat?",
  "response": "As of 2023, the state of Gujarat in India is home to **seven national parks**. These protected areas are renowned for their unique wildlife, diverse ecosystems, and natural beauty. Here is a list of Gujarat's national parks:\n\n1. **Gir National Park**\n   - **Location:** Junagadh and Porbandar districts\n   - **Highlights:** Home to the last remaining population of Asiatic lions (Panthera leo persica), as well as leopards, sambar deer, and various bird species.\n\n2. **Blackbuck National Park (Velavadar)**\n   - **Location:** Bhavnagar district\n   - **Highlights:** Famous for its large population of blackbuck antelopes, as well as various birds, leopards, and other wildlife.\n\n3. **Marine National Park**\n   - **Location:** Gulf of Kutch, along the coastline of the Kathiawar Peninsula\n   - **Highlights:** India's first marine national park, it encompasses mangroves, coral reefs, and a rich variety of marine life including dolphins, turtles, and numerous fish species.\n\n4. **Vansda National Park**\n   - **Location:** Navsari district\n   - **Highlights:** Also known as Vansda Wildlife Sanctuary, it features dense forests, diverse flora and fauna, and serves as a habitat for species like the leopard, sloth bear, and various birds.\n\n5. **Barda National Park**\n   - **Location:** Surendranagar district\n   - **Highlights:** Also referred to as Barda Wildlife Sanctuary, it is known for its populations of leopards, Indian wild dogs (dhole), sloth bears, and a variety of birds and reptiles.\n\n6. **Satpura National Park**\n   - **Location:** Bharuch district\n   - **Highlights:** Renowned for its scenic landscapes, waterfalls, and diverse wildlife including tigers, leopards, and numerous bird species.\n\n7. **Shiwani-Dudhia National Park**\n   - **Location:** Mahisagar district\n   - **Highlights:** A lesser-known national park that offers a habitat for various mammals, birds, and reptiles, contributing to Gujarat's biodiversity.\n\nThese national parks play a crucial role in conserving Gujarat's rich biodiversity and offer opportunities for eco-tourism, wildlife photography, and nature enthusiasts to experience the region's natural heritage.\n\n**Note:** Management and designation statuses of protected areas can change over time. For the most current information, it's advisable to consult official sources such as the [Gujarat Forest Department](https://gujforest.gov.in/) or the [Ministry of Environment, Forest and Climate Change, Government of India](https://moef.gov.in/).",
